From: Jack Heinlein <jaxxworkshop@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: rk3308: accept the RK3308B codec variant

The driver bails out on chip version B (RK3308B, GRF chip-id 0x3308).
Per the vendor driver, version B uses the same DAC mode/IO register
layout as version A (the RK3308BS_* layout is selected only on version
C) and the version-C-only digital volume registers do not exist on B,
so the existing version plumbing already does the right thing for B -
only the early -EINVAL return stands in the way. Drop it.

Tested on a Luckfox Nova (RK3308B): capture from the internal codec
works.

---
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/rk3308_codec.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/rk3308_codec.c
@@ -854,7 +854,7 @@
 		break;
 	case 0x3308:
 		rk3308->codec_ver = ACODEC_VERSION_B;
-		return dev_err_probe(rk3308->dev, -EINVAL, "Chip version B not supported\n");
+		break;
 	case 0x3308c:
 		rk3308->codec_ver = ACODEC_VERSION_C;
 		break;
